Jig is used to hold your grip blanks firmly while you profile, sand, finish and polish your own custom 1911 grips. These will firmly hold both full size and officers/compact 1911 grips.

The jig features brass pins that will not damage your sanding belt or disk and will not create a spark. I have the height set at .275 to .285. This will allow you to sand to the pins and be just thicker than the .250 - .270 final thickness. (Standard Grips)

title: For Sale:  Remington USMC 40X U.S.M.C. .22LR Military Trainer 40 x
postcontent:
In the 1950's, the U.S.M.C. ordered approx. 2200 top of the line rimfire single shot target rifles from Remington, the model 40X. These rifles were used to train Marine Corps snipers. They are easily identified by the factory stamp "U.S.M.C. Property" on the receiver. 

After the Marines finished with them, many were sent out to schools with shooting programs and eventually returned to the government. Depending on when they were returned, many were destroyed. Over the years a quantity were released through a government agency to promote shooting (the CMP). As you can imagine they were in rough shape and the demand far outweighed supply. You entered a lottery for a chance to purchase one and condition was not guaranteed. The CMP removed all the bolts and inspected the rifles then headspaced each rifle without regard to matching the bolts. 

Non-matching bolt. This rifle is in very nice condition. I had my choice of several and picked the best one. It is unrestored and with some TLC could be the highlight of your collection.

Two years ago the USMC 40X rifles sold for 1100, Last year they were 1300 and recent sales have been in the 1600 range. Excellent examples bring in close to 2000. It is collectible and will continue to increase in value. As an investment, its hard to beat this particular rifle.

I'm not interested in any offers or trades for this rifle. If you know what this is, you will happily pay the full asking price and feel very good about it knowing it will continue to increase in value.

It's a good shooter. This rifle is used and has dings in the stock. It needs a good cleaning. There are worn spots in the bluing. The scope and mounts are not included. 

Call or text 438 three I nine I during reasonable daytime hours. Face to face sale in Helena.
